A medical doctor in Elgeyo Marakwet has asked the state to intervene after the county failed to issue her with an appointment letter since November.Salome Kamau yesterday said she was deployed to the county in November last year after completing her internship at Iten County Referral Hospital in August.&ldquo;I have been petitioning the county government to give me an appointment letter and posting, but I have never received any communication,&rdquo; Kamau said.She said she was shocked that the state was planning to hire Tanzanian medics yet locals do not have jobs.Kamau has been volunteering at the county referral hospital.Elgeyo Marakwet KMPDU chairman Lawrence Kogo said the union has informed the county but is yet to get a response.